      "path": "/books/al-kafi:6:6:110:3",
      "relations": null,
      "text": [
        " كَانَ رَسُولُ اللَّهِ ( صلى الله عليه وآله ) يَأْكُلُ الْبِطِّيخَ بِالتَّمْرِ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Ali Bin Ibrahim, form his father, from Al Nowfaly, from Al Sakuny, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘Rasool-Allah<sup>saww</sup> ate the melon with the dates’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "3. Ali ibn Ibrahim has narrated from his father from al-Nawfaliy from al-Sakuniy who has said the following: “Abu ‘Abd Allah, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, has said that the Messenger of Allah, O Allah, grant compensation to Muhammad and his family worthy of their services to Your cause, would eat melons with dates.’” "
        ]
      }
    }
